    • compose

      public Callback.Completable compose(Consumer<Callback.Completable> consumer)

      Returns a new Callback.Completable that, when this Callback.Completable succeeds, is passed to the given consumer and then returned.

      If this Callback.Completable fails, the new Callback.Completable is also failed, and the consumer is not invoked.

      Parameters:
      consumer - the consumer that receives the Callback.Completable
      Returns:
      a new Callback.Completable passed to the consumer
      See Also:
      • with(Consumer)
